The paper is about few-shot learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The use of embedding spaces and similarity computations suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the use of miniImageNet suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. The paper also proposes a new architecture, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The use of modulation mechanisms suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category.
